    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2025-01-09</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2025-02-03T16:22:40Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;This joint resolution proposes a constitutional amendment limiting the pardon power of the President.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The amendment prohibits the President from granting a pardon or reprieve to himself or herself, to relatives or members of the administration, to paid campaign employees, to a person or entity for an offense motivated by an interest of any of those people, or to a person or entity for an offense directed by or coordinated with the President.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The amendment also invalidates pardons issued for a corrupt purpose.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United States limiting the pardon power of the President.</title>
